The paper discusses network steganography and the embedding of hidden channels with micro protocols in digitized audio signals. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it involves concealing sensitive information. Additionally, the use of audio signals suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also mentions features such as dynamic overlay routing and performance optimization, which are related to software-defined networking (cs.SD) and information theory (cs.IT).
